			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The version 1.0.0 sends too much data about your server to us. More precisely, the whole content of the <a href="http://php.net/manual/reserved.variables.php" target="_blank" class="postlink">$_SERVER variable</a> is sent. Starting with the version 1.0.1, only the spam-related data is sent. Details are <a href="http://bbantispam.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=23" target="_blank" class="postlink">in the faq</a>.
<br />

<br />
To update from 1.0.0 to 1.0.1 just copy the new includes/functions_bbas.php over the old file.
<br />

<br />
By the way, here is the explanation why so much data was sent. I noticed that different spam bots sometimes have different data in the $_SERVER variable. I think that it is possible to understand
<br />
* what is the bot (XRumer, ...),
<br />
* what other forums are visited by the bot.
<br />
I'm very curious. Therefore bbAntiSpam was sending all the data to me for future analysis.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://bbantispam.com/news.rss" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://bbantispam.com/images/rss.gif" border="0" /> Subscribe to news</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
